The paper focuses on analyzing user behavior in MOOCs, specifically in online discussion forums, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper proposes a generative model for discussion threads, which falls under the category of Cybernetics (cs.CY).
